snippet.textDisplay: I am having an anxiety attack right now, and I think it is triggered by this song. I have a handful of people to reach out for, but I can't. I feel helpless having these thoughts-- that I am sick and something within me, the sadness that eats up my whole being will be contagious and eat my loved ones the same way. I wanna be alone not because I want to, but because that's the only way they won't get hurt the same way it did to me. I can't even send a message to a close friend about  this. I wanna be free from this. I wanna be loved, and feel love like how normal people do.

Leave what alone? I am sure there is a message here in the title for me. But there is so many angles in my life this message could apply to any of them.
I would gladly leave it all alone, just let me have my life back. I was just a college student that wrote out an idea. I understand now why you don't want it. But let me live the life I was living. You didn't have to envolve me, or hate on me like this.
